                    Some role playing games allow the player to change the course of the game by having conversations with characters and choosing different response options. This kind of system is called a dialog tree. Let's explore an example. Suppose that when you initiate a conversation with {{npc_title}}, you can choose from {{amount_1}} initial questions to ask. After {{npc_title}} responds, you have {{amount_2}} dialog choices to say in reply. When {{npc_title}} responds again, you have {{amount_3}} ways you can end the conversation.


Draw a tree diagram to display all of the possible dialog choices you could make.

What is the total number of possible conversations you could have with {{npc_title}}?


