                    Suppose you wake in the morning and are feeling truly indecisive. You decide at last that you want to wear shoes, pants and a shirt, and you don't care how they match. You look in your closet and count {{amount_1}} pairs of shoes, {{amount_2}} clean pairs of pants, and {{amount_3}} clean shirts.


Draw a tree diagram to display all of the possible outfits you could wear. 

What is the total number of outfits you could possibly wear?


